# Module cftObjAnimMng

The module cftObjAnimMng contains several classes to manage animated objects inside your game.

# Import fantomCX

# Class cftObjAnimMng.ftAnim

The ftAnim class represents one animation of an object.

# Method AddFrame:Void(_imgIndex:Int, _frameIndex:Int)

Adds a frame to an animated object.

# Method Update:Void(delta:Float = 1.0)

Updates the animation of an object.

# Class cftObjAnimMng.ftObjAnimMng

The ftObjAnimMng class manages the animations of an object.

# Method AddAnim:Void(animName:String, imgIndex:Int, _frameStart:Int = 1, _frameEnd:Int = 1)

Add to an existing animation. Image and frame indexes start at 1.

# Method CreateAnim:Void(animName:String, imgIndex:Int, _frameStart:Int = 1, _frameEnd:Int = 1)

Creates a new animation. Image and frame indexes start at 1.

# Method GetCurrAnimCount:Int()

Get the number of frames from the active animation.

# Method GetCurrAnimFrame:Float()

Get the current frame of the active animation.

# Method GetCurrAnimName:String()

Get the animation name.

# Method GetCurrAnimTime:Float()

Get the animation frame time.

# Method RemoveAll:Void()

Remove all animations.

# Method SetActiveAnim:Void(animName:String)

Set the current active anim

# Method SetCurrAnimFrame:Void(frame:Float)

Set the frame of the current animation. The frame number starts with 1.

# Method SetCurrAnimRepeatCount:Void(repeatCount:Int = -1)

Set the repeat count of the current animation.

*Details*

The default value of -1 means it runs forever. A value greater than 0 describes how many times the animation repeats itself.

# Method SetCurrAnimTime:Void(time:Float = 10.0)

Set the factor for the frame time of the current animation.

*Details*

The default value is 10.0. The higher the value is, the longer a frame is displayed.

